Creating Images with R

with a little bit of magick

Thomas Hodgkinson

2023-03-11

My meme

My meme is an original work lamenting the awful weather in Auckland in early 2023.

Auckland Weather

library(magick)

# Creating an original meme with images from the internet and blank boxes...

#Grabbing images from the internet
sunny_image <-  image_read(path = "https://cdn.travelpulse.com/images/dd5c4cc9-abbc-9ba7-4469-06bd6f49f115/d81a1bd9-1f43-4282-b5b9-705015efcf72/630x355.jpg")
stormy_image <-  image_read(path = "https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/z/2/j/5/q/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.710x400.4z2im1.png/1671437652124.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium")

#Creating blank boxes

text_box1 <- image_blank(250, 250, color = '#000000')  %>% 
  image_annotate(text = "What we wanted!", color = "#FFFFFF", 
                 size = 30, gravity = "center")
text_box2 <- image_blank(250, 250, color = '#000000')  %>% 
  image_annotate(text = "What we got...", color = "#FFFFFF", 
                 size = 30, gravity = "center")
  

#Scaling the images and adding text to them.

sunny_smaller <-  image_resize(sunny_image, geometry_size_pixels(250, 250, preserve_aspect = FALSE)) 

stormy_smaller <- image_resize(stormy_image, geometry_size_pixels(250, 250, preserve_aspect = FALSE))


#Creating my rows and stacking them

row1 <- c(text_box1, sunny_smaller) %>%
  image_append()

row2 <- c(text_box2, stormy_smaller) %>%
  image_append()

meme <- c(row1, row2) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

#Saving the meme as a png file
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

My animated GIF laments the fact that many people pronounce GIF as JIF. It is mostly text based but I grabbed an image for the letter J from the web to give it a bit more flavour.

Gif not Jif!

library(magick)

#Creating the building blocks of my Gif

blank_image <-  image_blank(500, 500, color = '#FFFFFF')

# Setting up my frames

frame_1 <- blank_image %>%
  image_annotate(text = "There", size = 100, gravity = 'center')

frame_2 <- blank_image %>%
  image_annotate(text = "is", size = 100, gravity = 'center')

frame_3 <- blank_image %>%
  image_annotate(text = "no", size = 100, gravity = 'center')

frame_4 <- image_read(path = 'https://imgprd19.hobbylobby.com/6/9b/d6/69bd666c6ba963a96634b77cda86c84095fa574c/1400Wx1400H-191999-a-0320-px.jpg') %>%
  image_resize(geometry_size_pixels(500, 500, preserve_aspect = FALSE))

frame_5 <- blank_image %>%
  image_annotate(text = "in", size = 100, gravity = 'center')

frame_6 <- blank_image %>%
  image_annotate(text = "GIF!!!", size = 100, gravity = 'center')

#Creating my vector of frames

frames <- c(frame_1, frame_2, frame_3, frame_4, frame_5, frame_6)

image_animate(frames, fps = 2) %>%
  image_write('my_animation.gif')
